  "text": "Recently we proposed a new way to look at the measurement problem in quantum mechanics [CITATION_1] . In this proposal classicality is a property of large quantum systems. The bound objects that we have been looking at in section 4 are of this type. Their rigidity is the property that makes them appear classical. Thus, it appears that there is a connection between gravity and classicality. Classical behavior requires bound objects which in turn imply curvature.",
